Business Brief -- Burlington Northern Inc.:
   Railroad Firm Expects Rise
   In '92 Pretax Operating Net
Gerald Grinstein, chairman and chief executive officer,
said after a meeting with securities analysts in New York
that he expects 1992 revenue to be up about 2% from revenue
of $4.56 billion in 1991. He said he expects the company to
benefit from stronger freight traffic flows in grain and
coal, and he expects lower interest rates to stimulate
shipments of forest products.